            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The experience at the principal's office was unsatisfactory. Despite the need for seating, none was provided for parents, with the staff\nclaiming they were not responsible for it. Additionally, they insisted on email communication for discussions, which poses challenges for parents who are not literate. This reflects poorly on the management of the school.\n\nI strongly advise against considering admission to this school due to its poorly managed facilities and communication practices.\n\nIn addition to the inadequate facilities and communication issues, it's concerning to hear about allegations of mental harassment towards children and the lack of transparency regarding information. Furthermore, redirecting concerns to the counselor without providing clear information is not an acceptable resolution. These behaviors raise serious questions about the school's commitment to the well-being and support of its students.\nWhen you ask something to teachers she is responding so not dig into this. Is this a way to communicate to parents?\n\nIf the option to rate less than one star were available, I would certainly choose to do so based on my experience.\n#managementsucks",
          "publisher": {
